  <h1>
   draw_text_transformed
  </h1>
  This function will draw text in a similar way to
  <a href="draw_text.htm">
   <span>
    draw_text
   </span>
   <span>
    ()
   </span>
   <span>
   </span>
  </a>
  only now you can choose to scale the text along the horizontal or vertical axis (effectively stretching or shrinking it) and also have
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  draw it at an angle (where 0 is normal and every degree over 0 rotates the text anti-clockwise).
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_text_transformed(x, y, string, xscale, yscale, angle);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      x
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The x coordinate of the drawn string.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      y
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The y coordinate of the drawn string.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      string
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        String
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The string to draw.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      xscale
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The horizontal scale (default 1).
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      yscale
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The vertical scale(default 1).
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      angle
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The angle of the text.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_set_halign(fa_center); draw_set_valign(fa_middle);
 image_angle += 1; draw_text_transformed(room_width / 2, room_height / 2, "GAME OVER!", 2, 2, image_angle);
</code></pre>
  The above code will draw the given text in the middle of the room, spinning round and scaled to twice its original size.
 </body>
